Clark Sellick ( 1998 : 224 , fig. 34 A ) briefly described the micropylar plate and figured the egg of
D. australis
, but no formal description and illustration have so far been published. Several authors (e.g.
Etheridge, 1889
;
Lea, 1916
;
McAlpine, 1967
;
Priddel et al., 2003
) have dealt with the biology and natural habitats of
D. australis
on Lord Howe Island and Balls Pyramid.
